#: src/index.md:20
msgid ""
"AI Agent Assembly is a governance layer for AI agents. It sits between your "
"agents and the outside world and does three things:"
msgstr ""

#: src/index.md:22
msgid ""
"**Enforces policy** — decides, before each action runs, whether an agent is "
"allowed to call a tool, reach a domain, or spend more budget."
msgstr ""

#: src/index.md:23
msgid ""
"**Tracks cost** — meters token and dollar spend per team and blocks agents "
"that exceed their budget."
msgstr ""

#: src/index.md:24
msgid ""
"**Intercepts unsafe actions** — catches risky calls (and bypass attempts) at "
"the SDK, network, and kernel levels."
msgstr ""

#: src/index.md:26
msgid ""
"It works across your whole fleet of agents and does not require you to "
"rewrite your existing agent code."
msgstr ""

