#: src/index.md:79
msgid "The three-layer interception model"
msgstr ""

#: src/index.md:81
msgid ""
"AI Agent Assembly enforces governance through three layers. You can deploy "
"them independently, and each one catches what the layer above it might miss:"
msgstr ""

#: src/index.md:83
msgid ""
"**SDK layer (in-process)** — the language SDK wraps your agent calls and "
"applies allow/deny decisions before any network request leaves the process. "
"Fastest path, but requires you to adopt the SDK."
msgstr ""

#: src/index.md:84
msgid ""
"**Sidecar proxy (`aa-proxy`)** — intercepts outbound HTTPS using a per-host "
"CA, so it can govern agents that do not use the SDK. No code changes "
"required."
msgstr ""

#: src/index.md:85
msgid ""
"**eBPF sensor (`aa-ebpf`)** — kernel-level hooks that watch SSL libraries "
"and process syscalls to catch bypass attempts at the OS level. Linux only."
msgstr ""

#: src/index.md:87
msgid ""
"All three layers report to the **gateway**, which evaluates policy and "
"tracks per-team budgets."
msgstr ""

#: src/index.md:89
msgid ""
"These three interception points describe _where_ enforcement happens; they "
"sit inside the **Boundary** layer of the broader [five-layer defense "
"model](security-model.md), which describes _what_ is protected. Same system, "
"two views."
msgstr ""

