#: src/docker-containers.md:3
msgid ""
"This page is the reference for **running AI Agent Assembly from published "
"container images** — which images exist, how they are tagged, how to pull "
"and run the gateway and runtime, how to build your own agent image on top of "
"the SDK base images, and how to wire the governed agent + sidecar + gateway "
"topology so it works out of the box."
msgstr ""

#: src/docker-containers.md:9
msgid ""
"**Scope: this covers the limited-function OSS self-host stack, not the "
"managed SaaS.** The Apache-2.0 images below let you stand up the enforcement "
"data plane locally for evaluation and development. **Full functionality — "
"team budgets, the central registry, the operator dashboard, persistence, "
"SSO/SCIM — remains SaaS-only.** See [Open core "
"boundary](open-core-boundary.md) for the split and [Cloud "
"Deployment](cloud-deployment.md) for the managed platform. This is not a "
"production orchestration guide (no Helm / Terraform / Kubernetes)."
msgstr ""

