#: src/self-host-observability.md:29
msgid "Health and readiness probes"
msgstr ""

#: src/self-host-observability.md:31
msgid "`aa-runtime` — `/health` and `/ready`"
msgstr ""

#: src/self-host-observability.md:33
msgid ""
"The runtime runs a combined health/metrics HTTP server bound to "
"`AA_METRICS_ADDR` (see [Metrics endpoint](#prometheus-metrics-endpoint) "
"below for the env var and its default). It serves two probe routes:"
msgstr ""

#: src/self-host-observability.md:35
msgid ""
"**`GET /health`** — liveness. Returns `200 OK` with a JSON body reporting "
"`status`, process uptime, events processed, and which enforcement layers are "
"active or degraded. Use this as a liveness probe."
msgstr ""

#: src/self-host-observability.md:36
msgid ""
"**`GET /ready`** — readiness. Returns `200 OK` (body `ready`) once the "
"runtime is ready to accept work, or `503 Service Unavailable` (body `not "
"ready`) before then. Use this as a readiness/startup gate."
msgstr ""

#: src/self-host-observability.md:38
msgid ""
"```console\n"
"$ curl -fsS http://localhost:8080/health\n"
"{\"status\":\"healthy\",\"uptime_secs\":42, ...}\n"
"\n"
"$ curl -fsS http://localhost:8080/ready\n"
"ready\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/self-host-observability.md:46
msgid "`aa-gateway` — TCP liveness on `:50051`"
msgstr ""

#: src/self-host-observability.md:48
msgid ""
"In the [container topology](docker-containers.md#the-governed-topology) the "
"gateway runs in **legacy gRPC mode** (`--policy … --listen 0.0.0.0:50051`, "
"no `--mode`). In that mode it serves gRPC only and exposes **no HTTP health "
"endpoint** — there is no `/healthz` to curl. Gate its liveness with a **TCP "
"connect to the gRPC port `:50051`** from the host (the `aa-gateway` image is "
"distroless, so an in-container `CMD-SHELL` probe cannot run either — see "
"[Docker & Containers](docker-containers.md#health-checking))."
msgstr ""

#: src/self-host-observability.md:50
msgid ""
"```console\n"
"# TCP-level liveness — succeeds once the gateway is accepting gRPC "
"connections.\n"
"$ nc -z localhost 50051 && echo \"gateway up\"\n"
"gateway up\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/self-host-observability.md:56
msgid ""
"A standard gRPC `grpc.health.v1.Health` service on `:50051` is being added "
"(AAASM-4759); until it ships, the TCP check above is the gateway liveness "
"signal for the container topology."
msgstr ""

#: src/self-host-observability.md:58
msgid "HTTP health (`/healthz`, `/api/v1/health`) — local/remote mode only"
msgstr ""

#: src/self-host-observability.md:60
msgid ""
"The gateway _does_ serve HTTP health endpoints, but **only when launched in "
"a non-default mode** — not in the legacy-gRPC container topology on this "
"page:"
msgstr ""

#: src/self-host-observability.md:62
msgid ""
"**`GET /healthz`** — process-liveness in **local** and **remote** mode. "
"Returns `200 OK` with a small JSON body (e.g. "
"`{\"mode\":\"local\",\"version\":\"...\",\"storage\":\"sqlite\",\"uptime_secs\":...}`)."
msgstr ""

#: src/self-host-observability.md:63
msgid ""
"**`GET /api/v1/health`** — REST API health in **local** mode only (`--mode "
"local`), mounted by the **same `aa-gateway` process** (there is no separate "
"`aa-api` container). Returns `200 OK` when every subsystem check passes, or "
"`503 Service Unavailable` when any is degraded; the JSON body includes the "
"build `version`, `api_version`, uptime, and a `checks` map for the policy "
"engine, registry, audit, and alerts."
msgstr ""

#: src/self-host-observability.md:65
msgid ""
"Local mode is a single-process dev topology, not the gateway + runtime "
"container stack documented in [Docker & Containers](docker-containers.md); "
"its HTTP port comes from that mode's own configuration rather than the "
"`--listen` gRPC address."
msgstr ""

