#: src/troubleshooting.md:23
msgid "SDK cannot reach the gateway even though a gateway is running"
msgstr ""

#: src/troubleshooting.md:23
msgid ""
"Connecting to the wrong port/protocol — the SDKs speak **gRPC on `50051`**, "
"while the gateway's REST/OpenAPI control-plane surface (used by the "
"dashboard, and what `AA_GATEWAY_URL` points at) is **HTTP on `7391`**. Port "
"`8080` is a _different_ endpoint — the aa-runtime health/metrics server "
"(`AA_METRICS_ADDR`) — not the gateway REST API."
msgstr ""

#: src/troubleshooting.md:23
msgid ""
"Point the SDK at the gRPC endpoint (`50051`), not the REST port (`7391`) or "
"the metrics port (`8080`). For a fully local loop with no external gateway, "
"run one yourself: `aasm start` brings up a local gateway the SDK can "
"register against."
msgstr ""

